cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of node disambiguation in networks, which is a common issue in various fields of computer science such as social network analysis (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of network embeddings is also a common technique in these fields, further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
